NAFDAC Ports Inspection Directorate, E-Clearance Unit

FGN TSA: Paying NAFDAC Ports Inspection Charges

Kayode John Olusola
November 06, 2015

E-Clearance Unit
Ports Inspection Directorate
National Agency for Food and Drug Administration and Control (NAFDAC)

Introduction: What is TSA all about?

TSA stands for Treasury Single Account.

It is part of the FGN's policy aimed at creating a single account for e-collection of government revenues for the promotion of transparency and accountability in management of public finances in the Nigeria.

Payments to NAFDAC for services rendered to clients now goes to the FGN TSA.

Paying NAFDAC Ports Inspection Charges

A circular BPS/CSO/CON/DIR/01/079 dated 25/02/2105 from CBN to All Deposit Money Banks stated that:

“The Federal Government's Independent Revenue e-Collection initiative will automate Revenue Collections of Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDA) directly into Federal Government's Consolidated Revenue Fund (CRF) account at the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), through the Remita e-Collection platform and other electronic payment channels”

All charges from NAFDAC Ports Inspection Directorate should now be paid through the Remita e-Collection platform. The payment platform is available online at:

  • http://www.remita.net

Where Do I Start..?

Note: This process applies only to NAFDAC Ports Inspection Clients who are included in the Online Mail Request scheme and have been trained to make self assessment of their transactions and request NAFDAC Invoice by mail
  • Generate self assessment of NAFDAC clearing charges on the Single Window Trade Portal
  • Send the saved xml simulation file to eclearance@hotmail.com and await your NAFDAC Invoice
  • Upon Receipt of your NAFDAC Invoice, go to the Remita e-Collection platform.
  • Click on

What Next..?

  • On the form that opens, type “nafdac” on the field Name of MDA and select the Agency name from the drop down menu

Then..?

  • Click on [-Select Service/Purpose-] to reveal all the e-Collection categories for NAFDAC
  • Then select USERS FEES from the drop down menu

So..?

  • Type the Invoice Number from your payment advice into the Description field

Then the next step is..?

  • Observe the breakdown of the charges you are expected to pay and do some little calculation.

  • Add the VAT (5%) to each cost item

50000 + (0.05*50000) # Analysis

[1] 52500

60000 + (0.05*60000) # Inspection

[1] 63000

25000 + (0.05*25000) # Radiation

[1] 26250
  • Ensure that the total of your breakdown is the same as the Total on your invoice.

I've got my VAT inclusive breakdown! So..?

  • Select items that correspond to your breakdown and enter the values accordingly

That was easy... Yeah? But...

  • Confirm the total value is the same on the NAFDAC Invoice

To proceed...

  • Type in the Importer's name in CAPITAL LETTERS as Payer's Full Name

  • Enter eclearance@outlook.com as Payer's Email so that a copy of the receipt of payment can be sent to NAFDAC for purposes of payment confirmation

  • Enter Payer's Phone as required to receipt notification of payment

Final Remarks

  • Review your form carefully to ensure that all the information entered is accurate.

  • Click the Proceed To Payment button to generate your invoice.

  • Print the invoice generated and make payments at any bank of your choice.

  • Be sure to quote the Remita Retrieval Reference (RRR) on the bank teller so that the bank cashier can post your payment correctly.
